        "username": "Sarah_Kirschbaum",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/9d8465/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2021-08-06T11:39:52.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I posed this question via Instgram and Facebook yesterday - my newest shipment of Hebrart BdB, disgorged on May 6, 2020, is labelled as Brut, as it has been in the past.  I was checking out William Kelly\u2019s review and saw that he listed an Extra Brut bottling, disgorged on the same date.  His review also seemed to imply, if I read it correctly, that what used to be bottled as Brut was now being bottled as Extra Brut, to the benefit of the wine as the lower dosage revealed more of the fruit quality.  So I wondered if Hebrart was now doing both a Brut and Extra Brut, and disgorging them at the same time, or if the US label just continued to read Brut, which would encompass Extra Brut anyway?  Further confusing the issue, I saw a picture of the label on CT listing Extra Brut.</p>\n<p>Responses on Facebook, referencing the Skurnik website, indicate that they do both.  William Kelly was kind enough to chime in and say he might have \u201cgot the wrong end of the stick\u201d and would also be interested to get some details from Skurnik, but reiterated that the dosage has been trending lower chez Hebrart in any case.</p>\n<p>A search of CT shows very little in the way of an Extra Brut version (4 bottles in cellars and no notes, which usually means a wine added by mistake, but could just be a new version) and Wine Searcher Pro doesn\u2019t have much to offer either.</p>\n<p>Anyone have more information?  I don\u2019t immediately see a website for Hebrart.  If he\u2019s doing both, and disgorging them side by side, I\u2019d love to do a comparison tasting sometime.</p>\n<p>Thanks!</p>\n<p>          <iframe src=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/CSNNaJoLGQG/embed\" width=\"480\" height=\"578\" frameborder=\"0\" seamless=\"seamless\" sandbox=\"allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-forms allow-popups allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox allow-presentation\"></iframe>\n</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 6,
